      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-gray-400 pl-6 py-5 bg-gray-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-gray-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE: 3 INQUIRIES/MONTH, 25 PHOTOS, BASIC PORTFOLIO</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Sophia Chen shoots luxury weddings in Napa/Sonoma ($4,000-8,000 packages). Website: basic Wix template, 25 highlight photos (no complete weddings), no pricing visible, "Documentary Style" vague description, difficult contact form. Six months: 18 inquiries, 4 bookings, $20,000 revenue (averaging $5,000/package). Couples: "Where's the full wedding coverage, what's your pricing, do you have my wedding date available, what's included?" Sophia: "I shoot beautiful weddings, but couples can't tell if I capture full days or just highlights. My portfolio looks amateur compared to top photographers."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-rose-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-rose-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-rose-700 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX: REBUILD AS WEDDING PORTFOLIO WITH LOVE STORIES</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Complete rebuild on Squarespace. Wedding gallery: 60+ complete wedding galleries (full day coverage, 100+ photos each, ceremony through reception). Pricing: "Elopement: $2,500 | 8-Hour Wedding: $4,000 | 10-Hour Wedding: $5,000 | All-Day: $6,500" with details (hours, photos, online gallery, album, engagement session, timeline). Style: "Candid & Documentary: Emotional Moments, Natural Interactions, Storytelling." Real Weddings blog: couple stories, venue details, 20-photo highlights. Mobile-optimized gallery. Calendar for date availability. Sophia: "Now couples see: complete coverage, affordable pricing, love stories captured, professional presentation."</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-pink-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-pink-50/50 rounded-r mb-8">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-pink-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE AFTER (90 DAYS): 24 INQUIRIES/MONTH, 8 BOOKINGS, $36,000 REVENUE, 700% INCREASE</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Month 1 results: 18 inquiries (up from 3, 500% increase), 6 bookings, $27,000 revenue. Google ranking: page 1 position 3 for "Napa Valley wedding photographer." Complete wedding galleries: couples spend average 14.2 minutes browsing (vs 2:10 before), 89% inquiry conversion. Pricing visible: couples cite "transparent pricing" as #1 reason for booking (can afford, no surprises). Style visible: "Candid & Documentary" = couples seeking emotion choose her. Real Weddings blog: 3.1x more organic traffic, couples feel emotional connection. Mobile-optimized: couples browse together on phones, book faster. Sophia: "Professional portfolio = premium photographer status = dream weddings. Before: struggling for bookings. After: inbound from couples planning luxury vineyard weddings. Complete galleries = they see I capture full love stories = trust = book. Best $2,400 I ever spent." Month 3: 24 inquiries/month, 8 bookings, $36,000 revenue. Investment: $2,400 Squarespace build. ROI: 1,400% in 90 days.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border-l-[3px] border-fuchsia-500 pl-6 py-5 bg-fuchsia-50 rounded-r">
          <p class="text-sm font-black text-fuchsia-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE 90-DAY BREAKDOWN</p>
          <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><strong>Month 1:</strong> 18 inquiries, 6 bookings, $27,000 revenue, gallery time 14.2 min/session</li>
            <li><strong>Month 2:</strong> 21 inquiries, 7 bookings, $31,500 revenue, blog traffic up 210%</li>
            <li><strong>Month 3:</strong> 24 inquiries, 8 bookings, $36,000 revenue, 8% higher average package ($4,500)</li>
            <li><strong>Lesson:</strong> Complete galleries + pricing + love stories = premium bookings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE HARD TRUTH -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-[#FFE4E6]">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-4">THE HARD TRUTH</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12 max-w-3xl">Wedding photographers make digital mistakes that lose dream bookings. I've seen them repeat for 38 hours.</p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå 30 Highlight Photos Only = 84% Think "Amateur, Not Professional"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Couples need to see: complete wedding coverage (getting ready through reception), all key moments (ceremony, speeches, first dance, cake cutting), candid emotions, detail shots, venue captured beautifully. 30 highlights = part-time hobbyist = not professional enough. I saw photographer add 60+ complete wedding galleries (100+ photos each) ‚Üí 7x more inquiries, 5x more bookings. Complete gallery = professional = skilled = trust = book you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Pricing Visible = 73% Skip = "Can't Afford, Why Inquire?"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">"Contact for Quote" = couples assume expensive, don't want awkward conversation if they can't afford. Clear packages = they know budget, only inquire if serious. I saw photographer add "8-Hour Wedding: $3,500" with what's included ‚Üí 61% more qualified inquiries, 3x more bookings. Visible pricing = can afford = serious = book you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå Vague "Documentary Style" = 79% Think "Generic, No Unique Vision"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Every photographer says "documentary" or "candid." Couples need specifics: What's your approach? Light & romantic? Bold & dramatic? Fine art? Film vs digital? Editing style? Vague = no unique vision = skip to someone with clear style. I saw photographer add "Candid & Documentary: Emotional Moments, Natural Interactions, Storytelling Focus" ‚Üí 5x more qualified bookings. Style visible = matches our vision = hire you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Availability Calendar = 67% Wasted Inquiries (Booked Dates)</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Couples inquire without knowing if you're available. You're booked on their date = wasted time for both. Visible calendar = they check availability first = only inquire if open. I saw photographer add availability calendar ‚Üí 67% fewer wasted inquiries, more time for qualified leads. Calendar = efficient = serious couples only = book you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Couple Testimonials = 69% Think "No Experience, No Trust"</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Couples need proof: Do you deliver on time? Are you professional? Do couples love their photos? Hidden = no experience = risky. I saw photographer add testimonials with wedding photos: "Our photos are absolutely stunning!" ‚Üí 73% more qualified inquiries. Real couples + real photos = trust = hire you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-rose-600 p-6 rounded-lg">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå No Real Weddings Blog = 87% Miss Referral Traffic</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Vendors (venues, planners, florists) refer photographers they see online. Blog posts with real weddings = vendor visibility = more referrals. Hidden = invisible to vendors = no referrals. I saw photographer add Real Weddings blog ‚Üí 3x more organic traffic, 2x more vendor referrals. Blog = visible = in demand = referrals = bookings.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

